<p itemprop="description">A senior content strategist leads content strategy development for complex programmes and services. They provide strategic direction on content approaches, mentor junior strategists, and ensure content strategies are integrated with broader organisational objectives and user needs.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead content strategy for complex, multi-channel digital programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop organisation-wide content frameworks and governance models</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Mentor and develop content strategists and content design teams</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic guidance on content transformation and migration projects</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead cross-functional strategy work integrating content with service design</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive content strategy innovation and emerging practice adoption</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish content performance measurement and optimisation approaches</li>
    </ul>
</section>

